title: Kevin Federline
summary: Kevin Earl Federline (born March 21, 1978),[1] sometimes referred to as K-Fed, is an American rapper, DJ, actor, television personality, professional wrestling personality, and fashion model.[2] His career began as a backup dancer; he became known to the general public later for a high-profile two-year marriage to American singer Britney Spears and the child custody battle that followed.[3]
